            "updated_at": "2010-05-02T12:31:08Z",
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "It would be useful to be able to have \"config\" as a threadlocal or global object. For example:\n\n```\nconfig = dict(\"some_value\"=\"xyz\")\napp = Flask(__name__, config=config)\n```\n\nAnd elsewhere in your code:\n\n```\nfrom flask import config\n\n@app.route(\"/\")\ndef index():\n    assert config['some_value'] == 'xyz'\n```\n"
        },
